        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 18 at 5:30PM CDT by NWS Grand Forks ND</headline>
        <description>At 530 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking strong thunderstorms along
a line extending from near McVille to near Sibley to near Ypsilanti.
Movement was east at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Valley City, Cooperstown, Finley, McVille, Hope, Aneta, and
Wimbledon.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

These storms may intensify, so be certain to monitor local radio
stations and available television stations for additional information
and possible warnings from the National Weather Service.</instruction>
